1
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:16,400
The snake will bite us
if you move.

2
00:00:16,467 --> 00:00:18,033
What are we going to do, Red?

3
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:20,967
When I say run, run!

4
00:00:22,533 --> 00:00:25,167
Go on. Keep on distracting it!

5
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:27,167
Let's run! Let's go.

6
00:00:27,233 --> 00:00:29,400
Your wife is in the west
precinct.

7
00:00:29,467 --> 00:00:32,567
She's been charged with driving
under the influence of alcohol.

8
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:35,633
If she has to spend the night
in jail, so be it.

9
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,800
I'm a little thirsty.

10
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:39,567
Water.

11
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:40,833
Wait, let's change
that bandage...

12
00:00:40,900 --> 00:00:42,200
No, don't! There's no need
to do that.

13
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:44,867
I'm okay. I checked it earlier,
and it's starting to dry out.

14
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:47,233
It might get worse
if we expose it.

15
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:49,933
You should have called
our friends for help.

16
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,367
I should not have
stayed overnight here.

17
00:00:52,433 --> 00:00:55,433
No, it was my decision to keep
you here overnight.

18
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:56,533
How dare you!

19
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,300
You should have filed
an attempted murder case

20
00:00:58,367 --> 00:00:59,667
against that woman.

21
00:00:59,733 --> 00:01:01,700
She should rot in jail

22
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:03,367
and shouldn't be able
to bail herself out.

23
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:07,500
It's enough that I got to show
her I won't back down.

24
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:11,867
I promise I'll find some
medicine tomorrow.

25
00:01:11,933 --> 00:01:13,533
You'll get better.

26
00:01:15,167 --> 00:01:16,867
You'll get better, Red.

27
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:32,933
Lord...

28
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:38,367
Lord, please save him.

29
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:45,867
Lord, heal him.

30
00:01:45,933 --> 00:01:48,567
Lord, please, help us.

31
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:52,667
Lord...

32
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:03,633
Lord, please help us.

33
00:02:04,733 --> 00:02:06,500
Please, heal him.

34
00:02:06,567 --> 00:02:08,433
Heal him, please.

35
00:02:59,067 --> 00:03:01,500
Hello, what happened?

36
00:03:01,567 --> 00:03:02,700
Did you find them?

37
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:05,800
Yes, I did. My guy is doing
his job now.

38
00:03:05,867 --> 00:03:08,133
That's good.

39
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:13,700
I won't be able to sleep
until I get my revenge.

40
00:03:13,767 --> 00:03:18,267
If it's up to me, I'll confront
her myself.

41
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:19,433
But my plans might fail,

42
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:21,133
and I'll end up in jail again.

43
00:03:21,233 --> 00:03:22,433
So what?

44
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,333
Your husband will bail you out
anyway.

45
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,700
He won't.

46
00:03:26,767 --> 00:03:28,667
Victor had enough.

47
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:30,900
And I don't want him to know
we're doing something

48
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:33,500
against that woman.

49
00:03:33,567 --> 00:03:36,367
Rina, you never hid things
from your husband before.

50
00:03:36,433 --> 00:03:39,633
And he doesn't even know
about our business yet.

51
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:41,433
Better keep it that way!

52
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,700
You fool!

53
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:46,333
Do you want to lose
your source of income?

54
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,333
Of course, I don't.

55
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,867
So you better behave!

56
00:03:49,933 --> 00:03:51,967
Do as I say.

57
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:53,833
Don't worry, Rina.

58
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,533
We'll make things
difficult for her.

59
00:03:55,633 --> 00:03:59,433
She only got out of prison.

60
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:03,700
But not from the hell
I'm going to give her.

61
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:45,500
Mom, Dad!

62
00:04:45,567 --> 00:04:47,700
- I'm sorry, Mom.
- Red.

63
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:50,367
- Red. Red, wake up.
- Mom, come here.

64
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:52,767
- Red.
- Mom, come here.

65
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:54,167
Red.

66
00:04:54,233 --> 00:04:58,000
Red, wake up.
Red, Red.

67
00:04:58,067 --> 00:04:59,500
- Mom!
- Red, please wake up.

68
00:04:59,567 --> 00:05:02,367
Red...

69
00:05:02,467 --> 00:05:03,533
Red, please wake up.

70
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,633
Red.

71
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:06,200
Red, look at me.

72
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:08,800
It's me, Yenyen.

73
00:05:08,867 --> 00:05:10,700
You're here. Red.

74
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:17,300
Red, can you recognize me?

75
00:05:17,367 --> 00:05:18,500
Red.

76
00:05:18,567 --> 00:05:20,500
Yes, it's me, Yenyen.

77
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:32,700
If you survive this island,
tell my parents...

78
00:05:32,767 --> 00:05:33,800
I love them.

79
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:34,933
No, Red!

80
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,433
You will tell your parents
that you love them.

81
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:38,533
You'll make it home.

82
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,467
No.

83
00:05:40,533 --> 00:05:41,900
Red.

84
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:48,200
Red.

85
00:05:48,267 --> 00:05:49,767
Red, you have to fight!

86
00:05:51,633 --> 00:05:54,433
We'll get to see our parents.

87
00:05:56,133 --> 00:05:58,133
Please, Red. You have to fight.

88
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,733
Don't give up.

89
00:06:02,867 --> 00:06:04,300
Red.

90
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:08,267
Don't cry.

91
00:06:08,367 --> 00:06:12,133
Didn't I tell you that crying
doesn't suit you?

92
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:17,833
Red.

93
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:19,667
- Yen, It's cold.
- Red.

94
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:21,700
- I'm cold.
- Red.

95
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,500
Yen...

96
00:06:33,567 --> 00:06:38,700
You can't die like Miss Vinluan.

97
00:06:38,767 --> 00:06:40,333
You have to fight, Red.

98
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:45,467
What can I do to help you?

99
00:06:49,633 --> 00:06:52,067
Take your medicine, Mom.

100
00:06:52,133 --> 00:06:54,833
It will heal your wound.

101
00:07:05,567 --> 00:07:08,033
The medicine.

102
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:09,033
Red...

103
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:10,700
there's medicine on that bag.

104
00:07:10,767 --> 00:07:13,033
- Red, stay here.
- Yen, stay with me.

105
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:17,100
Red, you have to be awake
when I get back, okay?

106
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,367
Stay here.

107
00:07:19,933 --> 00:07:21,433
I'm just going to get something.

108
00:07:24,233 --> 00:07:25,567
I'll be right back, okay?

109
00:07:25,633 --> 00:07:27,967
- Stay here.
- Yen, please.

110
00:07:28,033 --> 00:07:30,100
- Don't leave me.
- I'll be right back.

111
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:33,367
Yen, please.

112
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:35,433
I'm just going to get something.

113
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:36,933
Yen!

114
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:00,533
Open the door!

115
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:06,700
Mrs. Castro?

116
00:08:06,767 --> 00:08:08,833
What brings you here so early?

117
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:11,500
I paid my rent this month
already.

118
00:08:11,567 --> 00:08:16,033
I heard that you're letting
an ex-convict stay in my house.

119
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,533
Is that true?

120
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,933
Ma'am, let me explain.

121
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:24,400
We never agreed that you could
let a criminal stay in my house.

122
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:27,067
Wait! You can't barge in here
just like that.

123
00:08:27,133 --> 00:08:29,200
I paid my rent already!

124
00:08:29,267 --> 00:08:31,233
I have a right in this house.

125
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:34,500
Can you please hear me out?

126
00:08:34,567 --> 00:08:36,467
I'm not an ex-convict.

127
00:08:36,533 --> 00:08:38,100
I got acquitted.

128
00:08:38,167 --> 00:08:39,933
I'm innocent.

129
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,867
But you spent time in jail,
didn't you?

130
00:08:42,933 --> 00:08:45,000
So you're still an ex-con.

131
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:52,667
Hey! Hey, you guys!

132
00:09:52,733 --> 00:09:55,500
Do you want to live next
to an ex-convict?

133
00:09:55,567 --> 00:09:58,033
Ma'am, you're out of line!

134
00:09:58,100 --> 00:10:00,400
This is wrong!

135
00:10:00,467 --> 00:10:02,033
I paid my rent already.

136
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:04,233
And now you're trying
to evict me?

137
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,900
Oh, really? Is that it?

138
00:10:05,967 --> 00:10:07,800
You keep talking
about that money!

139
00:10:07,867 --> 00:10:09,800
Is this what you're talking
about?

140
00:10:09,867 --> 00:10:11,233
This money?

141
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:13,267
Here! Shove it down your throat!

142
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:14,467
You know what?

143
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:17,000
This is the first time I've seen
a landlord do something

144
00:10:17,067 --> 00:10:18,900
like this!

145
00:10:18,967 --> 00:10:21,533
How did you know that
I just got out of prison?

146
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:25,533
Who told you to kick us out
of here?

147
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,600
How much did she pay you?

148
00:10:27,667 --> 00:10:30,067
- Whatever!
- Don't point your finger at me!

149
00:10:30,133 --> 00:10:33,167
I just want you out of here,
now!

150
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:34,300
Right now!

151
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,133
Go!

152
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,167
Leave my property!

153
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,533
Someone's waiting for you, Yen.

154
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,200
You have to get through this.

155
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:59,133
Red needs us now.

156
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,733
We can't give up.

157
00:11:01,767 --> 00:11:05,200
Miss, it's not yet
the end of the world.

158
00:11:05,267 --> 00:11:06,700
Hang in there.

159
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:15,700
Don't lose hope, okay?

160
00:11:17,533 --> 00:11:20,800
The mere fact that we're alive
and safe...

161
00:11:20,867 --> 00:11:22,200
that we're not dead yet...

162
00:11:22,267 --> 00:11:24,467
means we'll get out of here,
okay?

163
00:11:24,533 --> 00:11:28,900
We can only do that
if we help each other out.

164
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:31,733
He's right.

165
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,733
You climbed up all the way here.

166
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:35,367
You can do this too.

167
00:11:35,433 --> 00:11:37,200
You can do this, Eden.

168
00:11:37,267 --> 00:11:38,967
Never give up!

169
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:09,700
We're athletes, right?

170
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:15,433
And we both know that practice
yields improvement.

171
00:13:17,433 --> 00:13:19,700
Never give up!

172
00:13:25,267 --> 00:13:26,267
Yes!

173
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:27,367
Yes! Yes!

174
00:13:27,433 --> 00:13:29,333
I got it!

175
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:26,467
Yes!

176
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:31,633
Red, wait for me.

177
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:33,833
Red, I'm coming!

178
00:16:20,567 --> 00:16:23,100
I should file a complaint
against Mrs. Castro.

179
00:16:23,167 --> 00:16:25,367
What she did is wrong!

180
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:26,433
I paid the rent already.

181
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:27,700
We have a right to stay here.

182
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:30,300
This is my home!

183
00:16:30,367 --> 00:16:33,267
Someone paid her off.

184
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:36,100
Only one person is capable
of doing this.

185
00:16:36,167 --> 00:16:39,100
Rina's such a horrible person!

186
00:16:39,167 --> 00:16:40,300
Put the bacon down here.

187
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:43,700
There. Thank you.

188
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:47,033
And I'll go get the coffee
cup...

189
00:16:53,367 --> 00:16:54,933
Done. They got kicked out.
The landlord has been paid off.

190
00:16:57,967 --> 00:16:58,900
- Hey!
- Good morning.

191
00:16:58,967 --> 00:17:01,667
Good morning, good morning.

192
00:17:01,733 --> 00:17:03,600
How are you?

193
00:17:03,667 --> 00:17:06,333
You seem to be in a good mood.

194
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,367
You know what, Hon?

195
00:17:08,433 --> 00:17:11,433
Our conversation last night
helped out a lot.

196
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:15,033
I woke up with renewed energy.

197
00:17:15,133 --> 00:17:17,533
To look for our son.

198
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,833
That's good.

199
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:21,233
- I'll call the airline.
- Yes.

200
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:22,233
They might have an update.

201
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:23,833
Okay, please let me know
what happened.

202
00:17:23,900 --> 00:17:25,233
- Okay.
- Okay.

203
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:57,467
Amanda, if I were you,
I won't fight back.

204
00:17:57,533 --> 00:18:01,067
If you do, she'll get mad again.

205
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:02,933
So this revenge will never end.

206
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,667
Wait, what are you trying
to say?

207
00:18:05,733 --> 00:18:09,033
That I should just let this go?

208
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:12,733
It's not like that. But Rina
seems to be out of her mind.

209
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:16,200
I'm afraid she'll harm us again.

210
00:18:16,267 --> 00:18:17,700
I've had enough of this, Dindi!

211
00:18:17,767 --> 00:18:19,167
I can't let her do this to us!

212
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:22,733
I suffered many years because
of what they've done to me.

213
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:24,833
I couldn't do anything back then
because I was in jail.

214
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:27,500
But the situation has changed.

215
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:29,467
I can confront them now.

216
00:18:29,533 --> 00:18:32,800
I can't take this anymore!

217
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:40,733
Red, I got the medicine!

218
00:18:41,767 --> 00:18:43,633
Red?

219
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:49,900
Red!

220
00:18:49,967 --> 00:18:53,200
Red, wake up!

221
00:18:53,267 --> 00:18:55,600
Red, you have to fight!

222
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:58,100
Red!

223
00:18:58,167 --> 00:19:01,733
Red! Red!

224
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:02,933
Rina.

225
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,900
Rina, what's going on?

226
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:07,733
Victor, it's Red.

227
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,733
I dreamed about him.

228
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,400
He seemed...

229
00:19:13,467 --> 00:19:15,767
lifeless.

230
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,467
I was trying to wake him up,
but he wouldn't wake up.

231
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:20,167
What does that mean, Victor?

232
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:21,900
Is our son dead?

233
00:19:21,967 --> 00:19:24,333
- Is he dead?
- No, no, no, no.

234
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:27,533
It's just a dream.

235
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:31,500
Most dreams don't come true.

236
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,900
It's the opposite in real life.

237
00:19:33,967 --> 00:19:37,867
But Victor, it seems so real.

238
00:19:37,933 --> 00:19:39,333
It seems real!

239
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:41,567
I was holding him.

240
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:44,800
I can still feel him right now.

241
00:19:44,867 --> 00:19:49,333
I was trying to wake him up,
but he wouldn't wake up.

242
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:52,800
Victor, I can't bear it
if something bad happens to him.

243
00:19:52,867 --> 00:19:53,833
I can't do it.

244
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:56,967
I can't bear it, Victor.

245
00:19:57,033 --> 00:19:59,900
Don't think like that.

246
00:19:59,967 --> 00:20:02,100
Our son will come back to us.

247
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,767
He'll come back alive.

248
00:20:14,167 --> 00:20:15,933
Red, you said you wouldn't
leave me!

249
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,367
Red!

250
00:20:17,433 --> 00:20:19,300
Please, don't leave me.

251
00:20:19,367 --> 00:20:22,433
Red, you said we're partners,
right?

252
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:24,200
Red!

253
00:20:24,267 --> 00:20:26,467
Red, don't leave me!

254
00:20:26,533 --> 00:20:29,267
You have to fight!
You have to fight, please!

255
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:30,300
Red!

256
00:20:39,267 --> 00:20:42,100
You can't die like Coach!

257
00:20:42,167 --> 00:20:44,000
Coach, wake up!

258
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:45,300
Coach, wake up!

259
00:20:45,367 --> 00:20:47,133
Coach!

260
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:49,667
Coach!

261
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:51,900
Red, wake up!

262
00:20:51,967 --> 00:20:55,300
Red! You can still go home
to your parents.

263
00:20:55,367 --> 00:20:56,633
I can still hug my mom.

264
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:58,700
We'll go home, Red.

265
00:20:58,767 --> 00:21:00,767
We'll go home.

266
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:03,000
Red! Red!

267
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,633
Red! Red!

268
00:21:13,167 --> 00:21:14,633
Red!

269
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:20,233
Red, you're alive.

270
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:22,867
I have the medicine.

271
00:21:22,933 --> 00:21:26,200
Take this.

272
00:21:26,267 --> 00:21:27,900
Take this, Red.

273
00:21:32,433 --> 00:21:33,933
Take this medicine.

274
00:21:52,533 --> 00:21:54,767
Thank you for not leaving me.

275
00:22:00,967 --> 00:22:02,533
Amanda, what are you going
to do?

276
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,167
Where are you going?

277
00:22:04,233 --> 00:22:05,333
To Rina!

278
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:09,767
I know she paid your landlord
off to kick us out.

279
00:22:09,833 --> 00:22:10,967
Wait, Amanda.

280
00:22:11,033 --> 00:22:12,733
What if she didn't do it?

281
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,333
What if she had nothing to do
with it?

282
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:16,433
You will only cause trouble.

283
00:22:16,533 --> 00:22:18,433
Amanda, please.

284
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,433
What do you want me to do?

285
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:21,133
Should we just let her trample
on us?

286
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:23,667
The same way they did when
they sent me to prison!

287
00:22:23,733 --> 00:22:26,700
She'll think she can do whatever
she wants if we don't react.

288
00:22:26,767 --> 00:22:28,000
That she can trample on us!

289
00:22:28,067 --> 00:22:29,700
She can hurt us!

290
00:22:29,767 --> 00:22:30,700
Amanda!

291
00:22:30,767 --> 00:22:32,100
She will keep doing this to us!

292
00:22:32,167 --> 00:22:33,633
I understand how you feel.

293
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:35,833
Because we're being mistreated.

294
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:38,300
But we can just find
a new house.

295
00:22:38,367 --> 00:22:40,733
Let's just get away from here.

296
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:43,567
You know how I hate trouble.

297
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:44,633
Even when we were young,

298
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:46,400
I never wanted to be
in any fight.

299
00:22:46,467 --> 00:22:48,033
Come on, Amanda.

300
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:50,467
Please, I'm begging you.

301
00:23:16,467 --> 00:23:19,433
Red! Sorry,
I didn't know it was you!

302
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:22,000
Wait, why did you get up?

303
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:23,100
Are you better now?

304
00:23:23,167 --> 00:23:24,300
You were about to hit me.

305
00:23:24,367 --> 00:23:25,733
You're all better now!

306
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,133
You're all better!

307
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:28,733
You're all better now!

308
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:33,500
Thank you, Lord!

309
00:23:42,667 --> 00:23:44,333
You still haven't heard
about Red?

310
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,400
They're saying the same thing.

311
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:47,100
That they're doing everything.

312
00:23:47,167 --> 00:23:48,600
I really want to curse out

313
00:23:48,667 --> 00:23:50,400
that search and rescue
operation.

314
00:23:50,467 --> 00:23:51,767
Don't do that.

315
00:23:51,833 --> 00:23:53,600
It won't help.

316
00:23:53,667 --> 00:23:56,167
Just focus all your anger
on Amanda.

317
00:23:56,267 --> 00:23:57,733
Remember our deal.

318
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:01,767
I want you to do that
as soon as possible.

319
00:24:01,833 --> 00:24:03,467
Hey, Dindi, you have to be here
early tomorrow, okay?

320
00:24:03,533 --> 00:24:04,967
It's your contract renewal.

321
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:07,367
Yes, Ma'am. I'll be here
first thing in the morning.

322
00:24:07,433 --> 00:24:08,700
Take care.

323
00:24:08,767 --> 00:24:10,000
Take care, Ma'am.

324
00:24:10,067 --> 00:24:12,667
We need to get out
of this island.

325
00:24:12,733 --> 00:24:16,767
Or else, I might end up
not having a boyfriend.

326
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:20,067
Why not get a boyfriend here?

327
00:24:20,133 --> 00:24:22,767
How can I do that?
You're the only guy here.

328
00:24:22,833 --> 00:24:24,100
You're lucky.

329
00:24:24,167 --> 00:24:25,100
Crazy.

330
00:24:25,167 --> 00:24:27,733
Who wouldn't go crazy over you?
